This paper is primarily focused on measuring personalization in Web search results, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses user attributes and features that cause personalization, which could also fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and methodology for measuring personalization, which could fall under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories.
